{
  "texts": [
    "SLPs routinely rely on technologies such as augmentative and alternative communication (AAC) devices.",
    "AAC personalization, through techniques like voice banking (Springer, 2019; Yamagishi et al., 2012) and custom synthetic voices (Bunnell et al., 2005), is becoming more prevalent (Cave & Bloch, 2021).",
    "Attempts at generating speech from direct connection to the brain are increasingly successful (Naddaf, 2025).",
    "Telepractice platforms for people with aphasia (Spelter et al., 2023), and biofeedback systems to support swallowing in people with Parkinson's disease and dysphagia are reported (Battel et al., 2021).",
    "AI has the potential to enhance these tools by introducing predictive text, naturalistic voice generation, and real-time performance monitoring."
  ]
}